    let coffeeText = ["Belgian is Belgium morning coffee and contains baileys, kahlua, choco, milk, espresso i.e served in cofee cups that give warm on the heat. Our mission is to source, roast and prepare the finest coffees at Lukla, creating a transaction that is mutually beneficial for all participants.\nAt Everest Burger, we will pursue constant improvement in coffee quality in a sometimes playful and always intellectually curious way, including those as yet unforeseen or unavailable. We will make every effort to keep our footprint with the visitors." , "The Everest Espresso is prepared in a small glass and topped up with hazelnut cream. The very first sip reveals this speciality’s two core essences: hot and cold, sweetness and strength, coffee and hazelnut.\n\nPREPARATION\nPrepare an espresso in a small glass.\nTop up with 30ml of Hazelnut Cream.\nDecorate with a light dusting of ground coffee.\n\nPreparation of Hazelnut Cream (8 portions):\nPour the double cream and hazelnut topping into a large bowl.\nWhip with an electric whisk.\n\nWe recommend preparing this recipe with espresso coffee.", "We cannot guarantee that any of our products are free from allergens (including dairy, eggs, soy, tree nuts, wheat and others) as we use shared equipment to store, prepare and serve them.\nAt Everest Burger we give a fresh start to your day. Enjoy our superior 100% American coffee, rich in flavor and aroma, from the best quality beans.\nDiscover our Passion for Coffee and let us make a difference in your day. Enjoy our Fresh Roasted Coffee at home or at work, using our suggested serving: start with a clean coffee maker, add 2 tablespoons (10g) of coffee for every 6 ounces (180ml) of filtered water.\nOur 100% gourmet coffee is export quality and delivers the unique and delicious flavor that has made Everest Americano the best coffee in the region.","Cappuccino is Italian morning coffee and should be served in porcelain coffee cups that keep warm on the heat.\nIf you want a lighter variant, you only use simple espresso.\nYou make milk skim either using a steamer found on the espresso machine or a milk skimmer. If you are using milk skimmers, you will skim the milk first, and heat it up in the microwave. Make sure the milk does not boil.\nThe milk should not be as stewed egg white, but velvety and dense, without large bubbles. The milk is finished when you have 50/50 with warm milk and milk foam.Serve with cappuccino spices, cinnamon or sugar only. It is up to you.", "We create an exquisite cafe-style mocha with our brewer - just combine our rich, never bitter Espresso Roast Coffee with our unique Mocha Latte Froth, made from real milk. A creamy blend of cocoa and coffee topped with a velvety layer of froth, our GEVALIA Mocha Latte is an authentic Kaffe moment at home.\n\nApproach\nHave the  espresso in a glass of glass. Then fill up with warm milk with a dash of  steamed milk on top. That is is actually all.\nIt may be possible to use condiments like vanilla and mocca, but the original is without it.\nIf you want a milder variation of this drink, you can prepare a Café au lait. In the French cafe au lait, for example, use strong coffee instead of espresso , which will give a slightly milder taste.", "Distribute whiskey and hot syrup into ice cream if it is heat resistant and mix well. Put a spoon on the surface of the sugary whiskey and pour in 2.5 cl of coffee while slowly pulling the spoon so that it formed a new layer on the whiskey.\nWhip cream and cream to the third layer, place the cream on top and serve immediately"]
    
